#### Issue details

Color.rgb888ToColor erroneously treats incoming color as ARGB instead of RGB.
#### Reproduction steps/code

RGB color is currently treated as ARGB by the masks:
    public static void rgb888ToColor (Color color, int value) {
        color.r = ((value & 0x00ff0000) >>> 16) / 255f;
        color.g = ((value & 0x0000ff00) >>> 8) / 255f;
        color.b = ((value & 0x000000ff)) / 255f;
    }

 Should be instead treated as RGB by the masks:
    public static void rgb888ToColor (Color color, int value) {
        color.r = ((value & 0xff000000) >>> 16) / 255f;
        color.g = ((value & 0x00ff0000) >>> 8) / 255f;
        color.b = ((value & 0x0000ff00)) / 255f;
    }
